                    Familiarizing the Sitter with<br />Your Family and Home</b></font></span><br /></div><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.25in; font-family: Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif; color: black; text-align: left; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 11pt;">&nbsp;<br /></p><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.25in; font-family: Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif; color: black; text-align: left; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 11pt;"><font style="font-size: 10pt;"><font style="font-size: 10pt;">Meeting a new sitter is an exciting experience for the whole family. It is important that the sitter is familiar with your home and has your information in case of an emergency. By providing the sitter with this information, you can rest assured that your children will be safe and secure. Below are some things to remember when familiarizing the sitter with your family and home.<br /></font></font></p><div style="text-align: center;"><font style="font-size: 8pt;"><br /></font></div><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.25in; font-family: Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif; color: black; text-align: left; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 11pt;"><font style="font-size: 10pt;"><span>When introducing the sitter to your family, make sure he or she knows:</span></font></p><ul><ul><li><font style="font-size: 10pt;"><span><font style="font-size: 10pt;"><span>Rules of the house<br /></span></font></span></font></li><li><font style="font-size: 10pt;"><span>Special needs of the children</span></font></li><li><font style="font-size: 10pt;"><span>Bedtime routines for each child</span></font></li><li><font style="font-size: 10pt;"><span>Medical concerns and allergies</span></font></li></ul></ul><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.25in; font-family: Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif; color: black; text-align: left; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 11pt;"><font style="font-size: 10pt;"><span>When giving the sitter a tour of your home, point out:</span></font></p><ul><ul><li><font style="font-size: 10pt;"><span>Where the phone</span></font><font style="font-size: 8pt;"><span><font style="font-size: 10pt;"><span><font style="font-size: 10pt;"><span><font style="font-size: 10pt;"><font style="font-size: 10pt;"><a track="on" shape="rect" href="http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?et=1103577355946&s=-1&e=001yHdAct-kLavs7iCR5Wx_pHfEFvAdXKbbxvBMZ4NUsWDYkY1NvaB3njGTAFtUU6SifB2RayH14wqi0OR_Q3IoroBcNLnextSTmPoTPXaHaMvcaa2NzuY0ZMcz6AB2U3ODrymLt7TxIfh1Yqt59yT_teeZUIBoxttN" target="_blank"></a></font></font></span></font></span></font></span></font><font style="font-size: 10pt;"><span> is located and how to handle incoming calls<br /></span></font></li><li><font style="font-size: 10pt;"><span>How to operate the security system</span></font></li><li><font style="font-size: 10pt;"><span>The location of the first-aid kit and fire </span></font><font style="font-size: 10pt;"><span>extinguisher</span></font></li><li><font style="font-size: 10pt;"><span>Favorite toys and games<br /></span></font></li><li><font style="font-size: 10pt;"><span>Off-limits areas</span></font></li><li><font style="font-size: 10pt;"><span>The list of important contact information</span></font></li></ul></ul><font style="font-size: 10pt;"><span><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.25in; font-family: Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif; color: black; text-align: left; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 11pt;"><font style="font-size: 10pt;"><font style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: rgb(12, 71, 157);"><a style="color: rgb(12, 71, 157); text-decoration: underline;" track="on" shape="rect" href="http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?et=1103577355946&s=-1&e=001yHdAct-kLavs7iCR5Wx_pHfEFvAdXKbbxvBMZ4NUsWDYkY1NvaB3njGTAFtUU6SifB2RayH14wqi0OR_Q3IoroBcNLnextSTmPoTPXaHaMvcaa2NzuY0ZMcz6AB2U3ODrymLt7TxIfh1Yqt59yT_teeZUIBoxttN" linktype="link" target="_blank">Click here</a></span> </font></font><font style="font-size: 10pt;"><font style="font-size: 10pt;">to download this form. It will provide the sitter with easy reference to these important details.<br /></font></font></p></span></font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.1732in; color: black; text-align: center; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;"><font style="font-size: 8pt; color: rgb(12, 71, 157);"><a style="color: rgb(12, 71, 157); text-decoration: underline;" shape="rect" href="#Top"><br /></a></font></p><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.1732in; color: black; text-align: center; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;"><font style="font-size: 8pt; color: rgb(12, 71, 157);"><a style="color: rgb(12, 71, 157); text-decoration: underline;" shape="rect" href="#Top">Back to Top</a></font><br /></p></font></td></tr></table><a name="LETTER.BLOCK13" /><table style="background-color: rgb(255, 209, 40);" bgcolor="#ffd128" border="0" width="100%" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0" id="content_LETTER.BLOCK27"><tr><td style="color:#333333;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:10pt;" styleclass="style_MainText" rowspan="1" align="left" colspan="1"><font color="#333333" size="2" face="Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif" style="color:#333333;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:10pt;">

